    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect bit extraction in PUCCH format 3 descrambling\n\n### Summary\nThe PUCCH format 3 descrambling function contained a logic error that caused incorrect bit extraction from IFFT output data. The bug manifested as corrupted UCI payload decoding when UEs transmitted PUCCH format 3 with high modulation levels.\n\nThe issue was in the `pucchfmt3_Descramble` function where raw IFFT complex values were being directly multiplied by scrambling bits instead of first extracting the sign bits and then applying descrambling.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/LTE_TRANSPORT/pucch.c`: Fixed bit extraction logic in `pucchfmt3_Descramble` function to properly extract sign bits from real/imaginary components before descrambling\n- Added clarifying comments to explain the bit extraction process\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder heavy network load with multiple UEs transmitting PUCCH format 3, some UCI payloads were being decoded incorrectly, leading to false ACK/NACK decisions and reduced link performance. The issue was more pronounced when UEs were at cell edge with lower SNR conditions.\n\nTo reproduce:\n1. Configure eNB with PUCCH format 3 enabled for UCI reporting\n2. Have multiple UEs transmit PUCCH format 3 with 6-7 bit payloads\n3. Monitor UCI statistics via the `dump_uci_stats` function\n4. Observe incorrect ACK/NACK pattern correlation values in the stats output\n\n"
}